  "prompt": "How do you know when you are going into the friendzone?",
  "response": "Recognizing when you're entering the friendzone can involve paying attention to certain signs and behaviors. Here are some common indicators:\n\n1. **Clear Lack of Romantic Interest**  \n   The person may explicitly or implicitly state that they see you as a friend and nothing more. For example, they might say things like, \"You're such a good friend,\" or \"I feel so comfortable with you\u2014like a sibling.\"\n\n2. **They Talk About Other Crushes or Relationships**  \n   If they frequently discuss other people they\u2019re interested in or their dating life with you, it\u2019s a strong sign they don\u2019t see you romantically.\n\n3. **They Avoid Physical or Romantic Gestures**  \n   They may avoid holding hands, hugging for too long, or any other physical contact that could be interpreted as romantic.\n\n4. **Plans Are Always Casual and Friend-Focused**  \n   Your hangouts are strictly platonic\u2014group outings, casual coffee meet-ups, or activities that don\u2019t feel like dates.\n\n5. **They Don\u2019t Flirt or Respond to Flirting**  \n   If you try to flirt and they either don\u2019t pick up on it or shut it down, they\u2019re likely not interested in a romantic connection.\n\n6. **They Invest Time in You, but Only as a Friend**  \n   They may value your friendship and spend time with you, but there\u2019s no effort to take it to a deeper or more romantic level.\n\n7. **They See You as a Confidant**  \n   They share personal details and seek emotional support from you, but only in a friend capacity.\n\n8. **Body Language and Tone**  \n   Their body language might feel distant or neutral, and their tone might lack the warmth or excitement that comes with romantic interest.\n\n### What to Do If You\u2019re in the Friendzone:\n- **Communicate Honestly**: If you\u2019re interested in them romantically, it\u2019s best to be upfront about your feelings. They may not realize you\u2019re interested or might feel the same way.\n- **Assess Their Response**: If they don\u2019t reciprocate your feelings, you\u2019ll need to decide whether you\u2019re okay staying friends or if it\u2019s time to create some distance.\n- **Respect Their Boundaries**: If they\u2019ve made it clear they only see you as a friend, respect their feelings and avoid pushing for more.\n\nRemember, being in the friendzone isn\u2019t inherently negative\u2014it\u2019s a sign of a meaningful connection, even if it\u2019s not romantic. It\u2019s important to focus on relationships that align with your mutual feelings and needs.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
